id: pm-7vm9
title: Accept positional title argument in pm create
description: "Agents naturally write 'pm create \"the title\" --type X' but the CLI required '--title'. Adding positional argument support removes a recurring friction point and matches the pattern used by update/close."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[3]: agent-ux,create,dogfood
created_at: "2026-05-16T16:12:05.486Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-16T16:12:36.671Z"
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: "Added positional [title] argument to pm create. Title can be passed as positional shortcut or via --title flag. Updated help text and error guidance to mention the positional form. SDK contract description includes [required] marker so help payload still flags title as required for type-aware validation."
expected_result: "pm create \"Title\" --type Issue works without requiring --title flag"
actual_result: "Implemented; positional title flows through register-mutation action, normalized via existing options pipeline, validated by requireStringOption with enhanced error guidance"
